# Test Connector

> **Status: stub — implementation pending.** Contract only. Uses the shared
> `connector-testkit` (Postgres testcontainer + auth request builders) and
> the sanity-test patterns generated by `create-connector`.

## Purpose

Prove the connector works before it ships: author and run the sanity,
OAuth, and delivery tests, and confirm the module set compiles. This is the
last service-phase gate before infra/registration and deploy.

Phase: **service** (verification).

## Inputs (from connector-spec.yaml)

- `slug` / `package_slug` — which modules to compile and test.
- `auth`, `identifier_groups`, `quick_settings` — what the tests assert
  against.

## Outputs

- Sanity / OAuth / delivery tests and a pass/fail test report.

## Human gates

- Local test execution only — no deploy, no live partner calls, no infra.

